		<td><b>Made a little NES game as a hacking conference challenge</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hey all, first time posting <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br />I made a little NES game as part of a hacking conference challenge - users got a &quot;.bin&quot; file and had to figure out it was a NES rom, run it, figure out the clue about a code being a Game Genie (and/or figure out what a Game Genie is and how to enter the code), before submitting their code to solve the challenge (each user got a unique &quot;.bin&quot; file with a unique code).<br /><br />People seemed to enjoy it and it got really good feedback. It even has a Konami code built in.<br /><br />I was able to make something far better than I had initially planned, thanks to dougeff/nesdoug.com's tutorials and free code, and even answering questions via e-mail. I'm sure I did a lot wrong, but I learnt a whole lot in the process (this is my first game - on any platform, never mind just NES), so just wanted to share it + the code, and say a huge thanks. Hopefully you'll see a bit more of me on here, as I might expand it further.<br /><br />The game:<br /><img src="http://i.imgur.com/xfIclmn.gif" alt="Image" /><br /><br />The code:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://github.com/hypn/bsides2016-nes-game">https://github.com/hypn/bsides2016-nes-game</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Thanks! HypnZA

		

		</td>
	</tr>
